[5, "Sad to say I have the same habit that I once read that the late great Christopher Lee had with The Lord of the Rings, which was to read it almost annually. I loved the film's, but the book allows you to join JRR Tolkien in his narrative through Middle Earth and see and experience the incredible diversity of personalities that the great man wove into a thrilling and classic tale. As well, who doesn't love dear old Sam, the real hero?", [101, 97, 224, 624, 4110], [10, 7, 19, 35, 319]]